-- U.K. Baby Boomers See Doubling in HIV Cases Over Seven Years, Report Shows
-- Kristen Hallam
-- 2010-07-20T23:01:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-20/u-k-babyboomers-see-doubling-in-hiv-cases-over-seven-years-report-shows.html

          
          
             HIV infections in Britons older than
50 more than doubled over seven years, the U.K.  Health
Protection Agency  said in a report today.  
 Cases among older people rose to 710 new cases in 2007 from
299 new cases in 2000, according to researchers at the agencyâ€™s
Centre for Infections who reviewed reports from England, Wales
and Northern Ireland.  
 Half of those over 50 were diagnosed with HIV late,
compared with a third or younger people, the agency said. About
75 percent of deaths among older HIV patients occurred within a
year of diagnosis, the researchers said. The findings were
published online in the journal AIDS and presented at the
International AIDS Conference in Vienna.  
          
          


  


        